(1984, 1, '2022-04-21 09:03:21', '2022-04-21 09:03:21', '<!-- wp:cover {\"url\":\"https://demos.ascendoor.com/ascendoor-magazine/wp-content/uploads/sites/62/2022/05/pexels-jimmy-teoh-1010657.jpg\",\"id\":2411,\"dimRatio\":40,\"customOverlayColor\":\"#000000\",\"minHeight\":100,\"minHeightUnit\":\"vh\",\"contentPosition\":\"center center\",\"align\":\"full\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-cover alignfull has-background-dim-40 has-background-dim\" style=\"background-color:#000000;min-height:100vh\"><img class=\"wp-block-cover__image-background wp-image-2411\" alt=\"\" src=\"https://demos.ascendoor.com/ascendoor-magazine/wp-content/uploads/sites/62/2022/05/pexels-jimmy-teoh-1010657.jpg\" data-object-fit=\"cover\"/><div class=\"wp-block-cover__inner-container\"><!-- wp:heading {\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"48px\",\"lineHeight\":\"1.2\"}},\"className\":\"alignwide has-white-color has-text-color\"} -->\n<h2 class=\"alignwide has-white-color has-text-color\" style=\"font-size:48px;line-height:1.2\"><strong><em>Overseas:</em></strong><br><strong><em>1500 — 1960</em></strong></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:columns {\"align\":\"wide\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns alignwide\"><!-- wp:column {\"width\":\"60%\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:60%\"><!-- wp:paragraph {\"style\":{\"color\":{\"text\":\"#ffffff\"}}} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-color\" style=\"color:#ffffff\">An exhibition about the different representations of the ocean throughout time, between the sixteenth and the twentieth century. Taking place in our Open Room in <em>Floor 2</em>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Thanks to social media, everyone knows that the village of Oia has the scenery to make your friends jealous. But that isn’t your only option, and we’ve got the list to prove it. Some of the following places to watch the sunset in Santorini are a bit out of the way or require some effort to reach, but that means you’re more likely to get the view to yourselves.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:buttons -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons\"><!-- wp:button {\"style\":{\"color\":{\"text\":\"#ffffff\",\"background\":\"#000000\"},\"border\":{\"radius\":0}},\"className\":\"is-style-outline\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-button is-style-outline\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link has-text-color has-background no-border-radius\" style=\"background-color:#000000;color:#ffffff\">Visit</a></div>\n<!-- /wp:button --></div>\n<!-- /wp:buttons --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column -->\n\n<!-- wp:column -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Look for Santorini on Instagram and Trover and the shots that really stand out are the sunsets. It’s a magical time for a magical place, bringing out the best in the island’s rugged coastline and clifftop villages of west-facing whitewashed houses. If you’re visiting the island with a loved one, there’s no better time to make a grand gesture.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column --></div>\n<!-- /wp:columns --></div></div>\n<!-- /wp:cover -->\n\n<!-- wp:social-links {\"customIconColor\":\"#ffffff\",\"iconColorValue\":\"#ffffff\",\"customIconBackgroundColor\":\"#3962e3\",\"iconBackgroundColorValue\":\"#3962e3\"} -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-social-links has-icon-color has-icon-background-color\"><!-- wp:social-link {\"url\":\"https://wordpress.org\",\"service\":\"wordpress\"} /-->\n\n<!-- wp:social-link {\"url\":\"#\",\"service\":\"chain\"} /-->\n\n<!-- wp:social-link {\"url\":\"#\",\"service\":\"mail\"} /--></ul>\n<!-- /wp:social-links -->', 'Discover the Most Magical Sunset in Santorini', 'Look for Santorini on Instagram and Trover and the shots that really stand out are the sunsets. It’s a magical time for a magical place', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'architecture-that-will-take-your-breath-away', '', '', '2023-10-28 19:06:56', '2023-10-29 00:06:56', '', 0, 'https://demos.ascendoor.com/ascendoor-magazine-pro/?p=1984', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1988, 1, '2022-04-21 09:08:44', '2022-04-21 09:08:44', 'Rome is a city with layers. Literally. Stretching back thousands of years, the ancient Italian capital has been built and rebuilt, sieged and sacked, and rebuilt some more. Its history is linked to countless world-changing events over the past 2,500 years, intricately connecting it to the entirety of Western civilization. (They don’t call it the Eternal City for nothing.)\n\nWandering through Rome and you little stumbled upon everywhere you go as there’s some ancient column or area that built around. In fact, it takes so long to build anything in the city because every time they try to build a subway, building, or change something, they stumble across new ruins and have to send in the archeologists to investigate.\n\n<img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-1989\" src=\"http://demos.ascendoor.com/ascendoor-magazine/wp-content/uploads/sites/62/2022/04/architecture-structure-monument-europe-arch-column-571996-pxhere.com_-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" /> <img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-1990\" src=\"http://demos.ascendoor.com/ascendoor-magazine/wp-content/uploads/sites/62/2022/04/architecture-building-chateau-palace-monument-cityscape-1326523-pxhere.com_-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" />\n\n&nbsp;', 'The Best Walking Tours In Rome', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-best-walking-tours-in-rome', '', '', '2023-10-28 19:06:56', '2023-10-29 00:06:56', '', 0, 'https://demos.ascendoor.com/ascendoor-magazine-pro/?p=1988', 0, 'post', '', 0),
