(2724, 1, '2023-10-28 18:29:52', '2023-10-28 23:29:52', '<!-- wp:cover {\"url\":\"http://klutchproducts.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/pexels-alex-azabache-3757144.jpg\",\"id\":2247,\"dimRatio\":60,\"focalPoint\":{\"x\":\"0.50\",\"y\":\"0.52\"},\"minHeight\":800,\"contentPosition\":\"center center\",\"align\":\"full\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-cover alignfull has-background-dim-60 has-background-dim\" style=\"min-height:800px\"><img class=\"wp-block-cover__image-background wp-image-2247\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://klutchproducts.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/pexels-alex-azabache-3757144.jpg\" style=\"object-position:50% 52%\" data-object-fit=\"cover\" data-object-position=\"50% 52%\"/><div class=\"wp-block-cover__inner-container\"><!-- wp:heading {\"align\":\"wide\",\"style\":{\"color\":{\"text\":\"#ffe074\"}},\"fontSize\":\"large\"} -->\n<h2 class=\"alignwide has-text-color has-large-font-size\" style=\"color:#ffe074\">Beginner’s Guide to Natural Light Photography.</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:columns {\"align\":\"wide\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns alignwide\"><!-- wp:column {\"width\":\"55%\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:55%\"><!-- wp:image {\"id\":1925,\"width\":320,\"height\":214,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\",\"className\":\"is-style-default\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-resized is-style-default\"><img src=\"http://klutchproducts.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/natural-light-post.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1925\" width=\"320\" height=\"214\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"style\":{\"color\":{\"text\":\"#ffe074\"},\"typography\":{\"lineHeight\":\"1.3\"}},\"fontSize\":\"normal\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-color has-normal-font-size\" style=\"color:#ffe074;line-height:1.3\"><em>Each of these parameters may be tweaked to get the ideal exposure or the perfect balance of light and dark in your photos. If you don\'t feel comfortable modifying these settings on your own, you may always use your camera\'s automatic or program settings. <em>When taking a shot, shutter speed refers to how long the shutter on your camera remains open.</em> </em> </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:spacer {\"height\":24} -->\n<div style=\"height:24px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n<!-- /wp:spacer --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column -->\n\n<!-- wp:column -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Natural Light Photography Fundamentals<br>To capture beautiful photographs in natural light, you don\'t need to attend a full photography school, but there are a few camera settings you should be familiar with before getting started: </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Aperture refers to the size of the aperture in your camera lens that allows various quantities of light to pass through. F-stops are used to measure the aperture. The smaller the hole and the less light that enters the camera, the greater the f-stop. With a higher f-stop, more of the image will be in focus (think Ansel Adams). A lower f-stop implies less of your image will be in focus, allowing you to focus more on your product. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em> Fast shutter rates can effectively \"freeze\" action in a single frame, resulting in no blur. Slow shutter rates have the reverse effect, resulting in photographs that are purposely (and aesthetically) blurred. Depending on the effect you want, shutter speeds can be as fast as 1/100th of a second or as slow as a couple of seconds.</em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column --></div>\n<!-- /wp:columns --></div></div>\n<!-- /wp:cover -->', 'Beginner’s Guide to Natural Light Photography', 'Each of these parameters may be tweaked to get the ideal exposure or the perfect balance of light and dark ', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1918-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-10-28 18:29:52', '2023-10-28 23:29:52', '', 1918, 'https://klutchproducts.com/?p=2724', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2725, 1, '2023-10-28 18:29:52', '2023-10-28 23:29:52', '<!-- wp:group {\"align\":\"wide\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group alignwide\"><!-- wp:media-text {\"align\":\"\",\"mediaId\":1929,\"mediaLink\":\"https://demos.ascendoor.com/ascendoor-magazine/?attachment_id=1929\",\"mediaType\":\"image\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-media-text is-stacked-on-mobile\"><figure class=\"wp-block-media-text__media\"><img src=\"http://klutchproducts.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/work-from-home-post.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1929 size-full\"/></figure><div class=\"wp-block-media-text__content\"><!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Moving closer to family</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;For decades, working parents — and mothers in particular — have been calling for more flexibility to juggle their personal and professional responsibilities. Finally, a global pandemic forced many employers to give it to them. Office workers were sent home en masse to stem the spread of the novel coronavirus, along the way testing out their companies’ capacity to maintain operations with a dispersed workforce — and challenging some long-held notions about how productivity is best achieved.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div></div>\n<!-- /wp:media-text --></div>\n<!-- /wp:group -->\n\n<!-- wp:cover {\"customOverlayColor\":\"#ffffff\",\"minHeight\":616,\"minHeightUnit\":\"px\",\"contentPosition\":\"center center\",\"align\":\"full\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-cover alignfull has-background-dim\" style=\"background-color:#ffffff;min-height:616px\"><div class=\"wp-block-cover__inner-container\"><!-- wp:media-text {\"mediaPosition\":\"right\",\"mediaId\":2401,\"mediaLink\":\"https://demos.ascendoor.com/ascendoor-magazine/?attachment_id=2401\",\"mediaType\":\"image\",\"mediaWidth\":56,\"imageFill\":true} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-media-text alignwide has-media-on-the-right is-stacked-on-mobile is-image-fill\" style=\"grid-template-columns:auto 56%\"><figure class=\"wp-block-media-text__media\" style=\"background-image:url(https://demos.ascendoor.com/ascendoor-magazine/wp-content/uploads/sites/62/2022/05/pexels-andrea-piacquadio-789822-1.jpg);background-position:50% 50%\"><img src=\"https://demos.ascendoor.com/ascendoor-magazine/wp-content/uploads/sites/62/2022/05/pexels-andrea-piacquadio-789822-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2401 size-full\"/></figure><div class=\"wp-block-media-text__content\"><!-- wp:heading {\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"32px\"},\"color\":{\"text\":\"#000000\"}}} -->\n<h2 class=\"has-text-color\" style=\"color:#000000;font-size:32px\">Working While Traveling</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"fontSize\":\"17px\"},\"color\":{\"text\":\"#000000\"}}} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-color\" style=\"color:#000000;font-size:17px\">For others, the biggest challenge to work-from-anywhere has little to do with the work itself. Helen Xue, 30, a communications lead, was living in San Francisco when the pandemic hit and relocated to Portland to be near her partner’s family. With the permanent policy in place, they recently moved again to Seattle. Being a digital nomad may be the dream job for those who love to travel. However, finding (and managing!) a job that fits your personality, goals, and adventurous lifestyle is no easy feat. This is how I balance working and traveling around the world.Remote work trips clearly are&nbsp;<strong>not the same as a vacation</strong>, but they&nbsp;<em>are&nbsp;</em>a great way to hack around your normal holiday limitations and to enjoy a bit more freedom.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:buttons -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons\"><!-- wp:button {\"style\":{\"border\":{\"radius\":0}},\"className\":\"is-style-fill\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-button is-style-fill\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link no-border-radius\">Learn more</a></div>\n<!-- /wp:button --></div>\n<!-- /wp:buttons --></div></div>\n<!-- /wp:media-text --></div></div>\n<!-- /wp:cover -->', 'How Work From Home Spurred Employee To Move Around The World', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '1913-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-10-28 18:29:52', '2023-10-28 23:29:52', '', 1913, 'https://klutchproducts.com/?p=2725', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
